CatDescriptText: Francis Edward, 1705 Boulevard of the Allies, was part of the "Pittsburghers Speak Up" column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 23, 1958, pg. A1 with question: "In the coming November elections, do you think voters should elect another Democratic Governor or change to a Republican?" answer reads: "I'm strictly Democratic so you know how I feel. There should be another Democratic Governor."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Francis Edward wearing eyeglasses and oval patterned dress, holding paper bag, wallet, and keys, standing on sidewalk of street, possibly Frankstown Avenue in East Liberty, with automobiles, street car tracks, and businesses, including one on right with sign reading "Ba... WORLD..." and "RUGS $1.89"
